    "what_description": "Aloe vera is a succulent plant belonging to the family Asphodelaceae, native to Africa and the Mediterranean region. It has thick, fleshy leaves with a green color and white or yellow spots, measuring 10-40 cm in length, and a rosette shape. The leaves contain 10-20 triangular, pointed segments, also known as leaflets, which are densely packed and have a wavy or serrated margin. Aloe vera produces a tall, red or yellow inflorescence, often exceeding 1 meter in height, with tubular flowers, and it typically blooms in summer. The plant has a thick, water-storing stem and roots, allowing it to survive in arid environments.",
