    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Aloe vera are its antimicrobial action, which inhibits the growth of bacteria, fungi, and viruses, protecting against infections and promoting wound healing, largely due to its high content of flavonoids and saponins. Additionally, Aloe vera's antioxidant properties play a crucial role in reducing oxidative stress and preventing cell damage by scavenging free radicals, primarily through the action of vitamins A, C, and E. Moreover, the anti-inflammatory properties of Aloe vera have been found to alleviate inflammation and pain by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, such as COX-2, which are responsible for the analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects of the plant. Furthermore, Aloe vera's hemostatic properties help to promote blood clotting and stop bleeding, mainly due to the presence of glycoproteins and other bioactive compounds that stimulate platelet aggregation. The presence of volatile oils in Aloe vera also contributes to its analgesic and anti-inflammatory properties, providing relief from pain and reducing inflammation.",
