    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Aloe vera are derived from its gel, juice, cream, oil, and powder, each used for various purposes. Aloe vera gel is the clear inner portion of the leaf, rich in vitamins A, C, and E, and is often used topically for skin conditions like burns and eczema. Aloe vera juice, extracted from the gel, is used internally for digestive issues and is a source of antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds. Aloe vera cream is a semi-solid topical preparation, often used for skin moisturizing and anti-aging properties, while aloe vera oil, extracted from the leaf's latex, is used for skin and hair care, due to its antiseptic and antifungal properties. Aloe vera powder, a dehydrated form of the gel, is used in various applications, including cosmetics and pharmaceuticals, as a natural thickening agent and for its medicinal properties.",
