    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Aloe vera improperly include experiencing diarrhea due to its high levels of anthraquinones, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation and stimulate bowel movements. This is especially concerning for individuals taking medications for diabetes, as Aloe vera can interact with oral hypoglycemic agents and decrease their effectiveness. Developing skin irritation is another potential side effect, as Aloe vera contains compounds that can cause contact dermatitis, redness, and itching in some individuals. Furthermore, using Aloe vera improperly can also lead to allergic reactions, such as anaphylaxis, in rare cases, particularly in individuals with known allergies to the plant. Additionally, consuming excessive amounts of Aloe vera can disrupt electrolyte balance, potentially leading to symptoms like muscle weakness, heart palpitations, and seizures, particularly in individuals with pre-existing kidney or heart conditions."
